---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'December 2025';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Privacy Policy" 
  description="Privacy Policy for Nahlawi Tools - We don't collect, store, or share any of your data."
>
  <div class="tool-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="tool-container privacy-container">
        <header class="tool-header">
          <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
          <p>Your privacy is our top priority</p>
          <p class="last-updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
        </header>

        <div class="tool-interface">
          <div class="alert alert-success">
            <strong>TL;DR:</strong> We don't collect, store, track, or share any of your data. Everything runs in your browser.
          </div>

          <h2>Introduction</h2>
          <p>
            At Nahlawi Tools, we believe privacy is a fundamental right. This privacy policy explains our 
            approach to your data - which is simple: we don't collect it.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-heading">What We DON'T Collect</h2>
          <ul class="policy-list">
            <li>
              <strong>No Personal Information:</strong> We don't ask for or 
              collect names, email addresses, phone numbers, or any other personal information.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>No Usage Analytics:</strong> We don't use Google Analytics, 
              Facebook Pixel, or any other tracking or analytics service.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>No Cookies:</strong> We don't set any tracking cookies. 
              The only data stored locally is your theme preference (dark/light mode) using localStorage.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>No Server Logs:</strong> Your input data never reaches our 
              servers because all tools run entirely in your browser.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>No Third-Party Sharing:</strong> Since we don't collect 
              data, there's nothing to share with third parties.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="section-heading">How Our Tools Work</h2>
          <p>
            All tools on Nahlawi Tools run 100% client-side, meaning:
          </p>
          <ul class="simple-list">
            <li>All processing happens in your web browser</li>
            <li>Your data never leaves your device</li>
            <li>No information is sent to any server</li>
            <li>You can use the tools completely offline after the initial page load</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="section-heading">Local Storage</h2>
          <p>
            The only data we store locally on your device is:
          </p>
          <ul class="simple-list">
            <li>
              <strong>Theme Preference:</strong> Your choice of light or dark 
              mode is saved in your browser's localStorage so it persists across visits.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            This data never leaves your device and can be cleared at any time by clearing your browser's local storage.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-heading">External Resources</h2>
          <p>
            We use minimal external resources:
          </p>
          <ul class="policy-list">
            <li>
              <strong>CDN Resources:</strong> Some tools may load JavaScript libraries from trusted CDNs 
              like cdnjs.cloudflare.com for specific functionality. No personal data is sent to these CDNs.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="section-heading">Hosting</h2>
          <p>
            Our website is hosted on a static hosting platform. While the hosting provider may collect standard 
            server logs (IP addresses, access times) for security and performance purposes, these logs are managed 
            by the hosting provider and not by us. We have no access to or control over these logs.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-heading">Security</h2>
          <p>
            Since we don't collect or store any data, there's no database to breach or data to compromise. 
            Your information stays on your device where it belongs.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-heading">Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Our tools are safe for users of all ages. Since we don't collect any data, there's no risk to 
            children's privacy.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-heading">Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            If we ever change our privacy practices (though we don't plan to), we'll update this page and note 
            the date of the update at the top.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-heading">Open Source</h2>
          <p>
            Our code is open and transparent. You can review the source code to verify that we do what we say - 
            which is nothing when it comes to collecting your data.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-heading">Contact</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions about this privacy policy, you can open an issue on our GitHub repository.
          </p>

          <div class="contact-actions">
            <a href="https://github.com/rnahlawi/tools-nahlawi" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              üìù Contact Us on GitHub
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-box commitment-box">
          <h3>üîí Our Privacy Commitment</h3>
          <p>
            We built Nahlawi Tools because we believe useful tools shouldn't come at the cost of your privacy. 
            In an age where every website tracks your every move, we choose to do the opposite. Your data is 
            yours, and it should stay that way.
          </p>
          <p class="final-statement">
            <strong>No tracking. No ads. No data collection. Just tools that work.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .privacy-container {
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .last-updated {
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .alert {
    padding: var(--space-md);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    border: 1px solid;
  }

  .alert-success {
    background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.1);
    border-color: var(--color-success);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .alert strong {
    color: var(--color-success);
  }

  .section-heading {
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .tool-interface p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .policy-list {
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: var(--space-lg) 0;
  }

  .policy-list li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .policy-list strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .simple-list {
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: var(--space-md) 0;
  }

  .simple-list li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .contact-actions {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .commitment-box {
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .commitment-box h3 {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .commitment-box p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .final-statement {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
  }

  .final-statement strong {
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }
</style>